- Identify that $\vec{v} = -3\vec{w}$ by comparing components:
  $$
  \begin{aligned}
  \vec{w} &= \vec{i} + 4\vec{j} - 2\vec{k} \\
  \vec{v} &= -3\vec{i} - 12\vec{j} + 6\vec{k}
  \end{aligned}
  $$

- Since $\vec{v}$ is a scalar multiple of $\vec{w}$, the vectors are parallel <marks>A1</marks>

1 mark total

<note>Accept valid alternative explanations that show understanding of parallel vectors being scalar multiples of each other</note>

